animal.description:
Take this Houston husky on your mountain adventures! Scully is a truly good boy who wants to please at his core. He's very smart and learned to "sit" very quickly without any prior training. He likes walks and I'm sure he could go even further if it weren't 70 degrees in December here. We had to take breaks to give him pets and love to keep going. Scully is a very excited boy and can be a bit mouthy when he wants affection. He will nip at heels and pants and will need redirection to stop this behavior. He has a lot of energy and while he is dog friendly, he sometimes doesn't realize when he's being rude or getting in their face too much. He is good about alerting when he needs to go outside. GSD experience needed...Scully needs alot of mental and physical stimulation and we recommend a home with older children if any. 

HW+ simply means the dog has tested positive for heart worms in our screening process. We utilize what is called the fast-kill method which means we place the dog on antibiotics for 30 days and then administer 3 injections in increments afterward. The cost to treat heart worms is rather steep. However, thanks to our generous donors, we are able to cover that cost for our adopters so long as they go to our veterinarian, Red Rocks Animal Center in Lakewood.


	Approved Applicants may make the adoption fee payment by clicking donate above. Partial adoption fees will not hold a dog.
	Dogs adopted with our rescue come with FREE training from #GoodPup to help you build strong bonds from the start!
	If upon meeting the dog of your choosing at an adoption event you find that you aren't a good match, your deposit will be refunded minus a 10% administration fee.
	Adoption fees include vaccines up until time of adoption, microchip, spay/neuter and 1st 30 days of free Pet insurance. We are not affiliated with Pet First pet insurance. (you have to sign up for the insurance or it will not go into effect). 
	Adopters can go to our vet for medical issues that may arise in 1st 3 days of adoption. 
	The dogs in our care are fostered in Colorado, Texas, and New Mexico. While all dogs are picked up during our scheduled times, sometimes transport dates change due to unforeseen circumstances.

PUPDATE JAN-30-2021: Since the last pupdate Viggo's adoption fell through but I have learned a few more things about him. He is not great with cats. He will chase them so I've been using a squirt bottle when he does that and he's learning to leave them alone. He really only wants to play but Viggo is a very strong boy, even with a bum leg. He tries to play with his foster Mom's kids but they're mostly older so it doesn't work so well. His leg is doing better but he still has Dogtor visits that need to be made (which are covered by the rescue). It looks like surgery won't be needed but he night have a limp. He LOVES to go outside and run like the wind. He's really good about doing his business outside and will bark if he needs to do so. His favorite place is still on his foster Mom's bed under a fleece next to her leg or on her lap. He's a very loving boy.

PUPDATE JAN-13-2021: Well, Viggo went to the Dogtor and it looks like he's going to need a few more visits to him before he's ready to go to his forever home. We will be updating when that time gets closer. Since then, however, we found that Viggo tolerates some cats and other he snips at and chases, which has landed him in hot water with his foster mom. She's found out that he doesn't like to be squirted and he instantly stops. He's starting to play even with his splint on but hasn't quite mastered the steps to the bed yet. We will be updating on his health as we find out more and when he will be ready for his new home.

PUPDATE JAN-10-2021: Viggo is a very sweet, 21 pound, 7 yr.young, brown Min Pin mix. He came to us with a broken leg so he has to get that fixed before he can go to his new forever home. He gets along great with other dogs or cats. He likes to sleep on the bed close to his foster Mom and burrow under the covers. Stay tuned for more information to come.


Visit me, Jordan, Boss of EveryPuppy of the Universe, by going to the FluffyButts Rescue Resort link above.

Fill out an application on our website (www.fluffybutts.com) if you're interested in being adopted by this cute kid. It's the first step in the pawcess. 

ADOPTIONS: We don't let the fact that you might live out of state stop any adoption that's meant to be, but you MUST be willing to drive, or fly, all the way to pick up your new family member. We do not ship these kids on airplanes by themselves - we think they'd have a hard time getting through security without their rabies tag setting off the metal detectors. If the kid needs a health certificate because they're flying home, that will be an expense for the new family.

ADOPTION DONATIONS: When you see the adoption donation amounts, we'd like you to know that 90% of the time the donation amount doesn't even come close to covering that kid's dogtor bills. This is definitely not a money-making venture. We're usually so far in the hole but the impawtant thing is to get these kids the medical care they need and help them find the pawfect family. That's our top pawority. (I just can't resist using "paw" whenever I can!) 

POTTY TRAINING: Please note that we NEVER say our kids are 100% potty-trained. How stupid would we be to say something like that? If you're willing to be trained by your new family member, please fill out an application. If you're looking for a totally potty-trained kid, you may as well stop at the toy store on your way home from work and buy a stuffed toy because those are the only reliable ones to NOT potty in your home. There is a period of adjustment, not just for the new family member but for everyone in the house. You must be patient, understanding, and willing to work with your new family member. It can take anywhere from several days to several months. You must be 100% committed to this, it's a lifetime commitment. 

HUG AND KISS YOUR KIDLETS LIKE THERE'S NO TOMORROW. 

Please be patient with us - we're taking care of a lot of kids - our own and the foster kids - and we have families, homes and full time jobs. We're giving meds to the sick kids, playing with the healthy kids, and loving on all the kids. We're doing their laundry, trying to teach them manners and where to do their business, and cleaning up their accidents. In other words, we're just a little busy but we'll return email inquiries just as fast as we pawssibly can. Thanks!

WE PROCESS APPLICANTS AND SET APPOINTMENTS BASED ON THE ORDER APPLICATIONS ARE RECEIVED

, so while you are welcome to email

with specific questions, you will want to complete the

ONLINE APPLICATION

ASAP

,

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Lucy is a lean, mean agile machine! She has legs for miles! We believe she is a 1-2 year old Manchester terrier/ chihuahua mix. She can jump a 3.5 foot gate from a sitting position. Who knows what she can clear with a running start! This dog is so athletic she would do extremely well with an active family! Hiking, agility, running would all be perfect for Lucy! She is super smart and would excel at anything put in front of her!

Lucy came to us from Texas as an owner surrender. She was about to get spayed when her foster mom thought she might be pregnant. Sure enough Lucy gave birth to 3 little boys on 10/01/2020! The boys are ready to find their forever homes and Lucy is to! She was an amazing mom and so much fun. She made the foster moms job easy for sure.

Lucy is the funniest little dog. She gets along with most of the dogs in her foster home but can be a rough, dominant player. Some dogs love it and others don't so if you have another dog please take this into consideration. Lucy appears to be housebroken with a doggy door and fully fenced yard but we always say please expect accidents while she acclimates to a new home and routine. We would like to place Lucy in a home with a fully fenced yard (no invisible or electric fences) and no chain link.

Lucy walks pretty well on a leash and is good in the car. She loves her family and truly wants to do anything to please you. She can be shy initially when new people come over and sometimes will even bark at them but she recovers pretty quickly especially for a treat. She has been around children with no issues and had been in a home with cats and she was okay with them.

Lucy has been through a lot and is looking for her forever home! She is very sweet and extremely eager to please. She loves to be loved and will curl up on your lap for a nap or snuggle in bed with you at night. She listens very well and we are so excited for her to have a chance at a loving home. If this is with you please apply!

Lucy is spayed, up to date with vaccines, microchipped, flea/worm treated and tested neg. for heartworm. Her adoption fee is $400

animal.description:
Meet Mishti & Chutki, a sweet, friendly and loving bonded pair rescued from the streets of Haryana, near New Dehli, India and coming to America very soon. Like many dogs in India, their mom was homeless, living behind an office building in large office complex when she gave birth to 5 puppies. Their guardians discovered them when they were a month old and took mom and all her pups in to their office center so they wouldn't be killed by traffic. They took them in and cared for and doted on them as a member of the family. As you see in their video, they are two friendly, loving and happy girls. All the dogs have been rehomed except for Mishti & Chutki and their primary guardian wants our help in find them a great forever home together here in America.

Their guardian shares the following: Mishti & Chutki are approximately 1 year old and weigh about 35lbs, They look like hound dog mix but in India most strays are Indian Pariah or Pye mix. Mishti (Means full of Sweetness) is the golden girl & the brown is Chutki (Means Youngest). Chutki has a slight defect in her left front paw, but this doesn't stop her activities. Both pups are adorable, friendly, housebroken, good with people and very smart and eager to learn.

Chutki is bit shy, calm & laid back. She needs a little more effort then Mishti due to her shy nature. She follows Mishti's lead. She loves walks, playing with her toys,going up and down stairs, getting treats, and cuddling and being petted and told how lovely she is once she's settled in. She doesn't like to share her bed, however (go figure). She is so very cute and loveable. She is a happy girl and she doesn't let her deformed foot stop her from enjoying life.

Mishti is more energetic than Chutki and would be a great companion for those who like to do running or hiking as she is always full of energy and up for an adventure. She likes to play with toys and eats almost everything she's given, and loves dog cookies & treats. She is the braver of the two girls. She is curious and friendly but can be aloof and independent. Like Chutki, she needs a little time to get to know you and settle into her surroundings.

Mishti & Chutki are spayed and up to date on core vaccines. The adoption fee is $425 for each pup. Please note that training is highly recommended for all young dogs. As with all rescue animals, breed determination cannot be validated without genetic testing.

Visit WWW.LULUSRESCUE.ORG and click on the ADOPT tab for an overview of Lulu's Rescue adoption process.

Thanks for adopting and saving a life!

animal.description:
Meet Vlad! Poor Vlad was surrendered by his owners in South Carolina, but luckily for him he went to one of our partner shelters who took the very best care of him before sending him up to us.  Vlad has been neutered and is up to date on all shots.  He is a shy boy and takes a bit to warm up, but just needs a family to show him that the world is not such a scary place and he can trust people.
Vlad gets along well with other dogs and children and once he warms up all he wants to do is snuggle. He is about 2 years old and a VERY handsome boy.

**PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING**

If you are interested in adopting any of the puppies, our adoption fee is $495 ( puppies) $375 (adults) which includes transportation from the South and we do suggest putting a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several littermates.

**Please understand that we are a volunteer based organization. While our volunteers try to answer all emails/questions as quickly as possible, below please find answers to some of our most frequently asked questions. We ask that you please read these FAQ's to see if your question has already been answered before emailing additional questions:

- If a dog or puppy is listed on Petfinder, they are still available. Please do not email asking if they are still available. If a dog or puppy is still listed, then we are still accepting applications :-) We do not go on a first come first serve basis, but on best fit for the family and most importantly, the puppy or dog.

- We are taking our best guess on breed and size when fully-grown (or already an adult), based on the puppy's/dog’s physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. We rarely are able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. 

- Our dogs/puppies are either at our Adoption Center in Brewster, NY, in foster care, or are adopted straight from transport. An application is necessary to meet any dog/puppy. Often, dogs and puppies are spoken for before they arrive. Many people feel more comfortable with a meet and greet which we completely understand and respect, however please know you are taking a chance of that puppy/dog getting adopted by someone else before hand.

- The way to start the process for any dog or puppy is by filling out an application. Applications for foster or adoption can be found at www.snarrnortheast.org and by clicking either adopt or foster from the main menu. If you fill out an application, please make sure you answer all the questions in as much detail as possible and that you receive a confirmation email, otherwise we did NOT receive it.

animal.description:
Sweet Baby Mindy is still looking for her forever ho- ho-home!

Mindy is a 3-5yo medium sized Heinz 57 who is full of life & love. She’s maybe 32lb at most.

She is EXTREMELY FRIENDLY & loves everyone she meets! Mindy is also good with other dogs & has been around cats before & hasn’t seemed phased by them. 

Mindy is special needs but her handicap certainly does NOT slow her down one bit. Mindy is a Tri paw (yes we may have just made that word up) she has all 4 of her legs but is missing her right rear paw. Again.... this doesn’t slow her down at all.
She is presently in foster with five other dogs and out runs every single one of them. She is like lightening zipping around the backyard!

She is overall a pretty laid back & lazy dog around the house all day long but once it’s time to go outside she does her zoomies & then she done. 

She is housebroken & dosent require a crate when left home alone. She is overall non destructive (but warning she does like playing with shoes) & loves to sleep on the couch or bed. She is also a GREAT SNUGGLER & loves to have human contact!

Due to Mindy’s handicap she would do BEST in a home without tons of stairs & a fenced in yard. She can absolutely go up/down stairs & walk on a leash with no problem we just Recommend this type of home environment just to make things easier for her overall. 

Mindy absolutely will take advantage of wide open doors or windows and can be a little escape artist we are chalking it up to her having an adventurous side but for her safety doors and windows must be locked and if there are children in the home it is important to make them aware  that she can be an escape artist.


•Presently in foster in Northern Delaware

animal.description:
Meet Karen!

Karen is a beautiful and goofy 7.5 month old shepherd mix who’s looking for her forever home! Her sister Elyse & Suzie have both found their forever homes but now is her turn!

animal.description:
Ginger is a gentle, loving 7 year old Australian Cattle dog, husky mix looking for a calm home, with a single person or adult couple who will be home the majority of the time. 

She is a very smart girl who picks up training and routines very quickly.

Likes to be near her people all the time, like a shadow. 

When left alone, she will look for her person's shoe to bring near her for comfort - will not chew on or damage the shoe though.

Enjoys daily walks and short hikes.

Lower to medium energy girl, happy to lay and nap at your feet while you work on the computer, cuddle up with you to watch TV or hangout with you while gardening.

Loves belly rubs and affection from her humans.

Likes going to the beach and staying on the sand, but does not like any kind of water.   

She's not an incessant barker, but will bark at other dogs and unfamiliar people who come to the door.

Sleeps through the night in her bed, your bed or her crate. 

Not at all destructive inside or outside, even when left alone for short periods of time.

Ginger will only play with toys that you give her, especially her favorite blue octopus.

Dog selective and would be best as the only dog in your life. (lived in a foster home with non dominant male dogs her size)

Cats are unknown, but not recommended. 

Walks well on leash, but will react by barking and pulling if she gets too close to other dogs. This has greatly reduced with focused training. 

Knows commands 'sit, stay, paw, leave it, come.

Not a fan of strangers coming to the house or people stepping over her. So would be best if she was crated or put in another room when visitors come to the home. 

She has been very child friendly in her foster home, and loved to cuddle with the kids in bed or on the couch, but we are recommending a home without children.

Due to several moves this last year, since her owner passed away, she has anxiety on long car rides. A doggie seat belt or riding in a crate in the back is best or she will try to join you in the driver's seat. She has shown improvement and we expect that to continue with more positive car ride experiences.

She is very loyal and protective of her people. 

Due to that fear based, protection/guarding issue, she will need a dog experienced adopter willing to help her feel safe.

Ginger is 68 lbs. spayed, microchipped, up to date on vaccines, including rabies, heartworm negative and current on prevention. 

If you are interested in adopting Ginger, please complete an adoption application on https://www.westernaustralianshepherdrescue.com/.

animal.description:
Mea is a 2 year old Canadian dog that found herself in an Ontario shelter after an incident with another dog.  

She is about 80 pounds and a really nice girl, but lacks training.

She is powerful, so will need an adopter that can handle the strength of a large breed dog and you must come with large dog breed experience.

Mea arrived to the shelter without anything being said about puppies, but when she went in for her spay, she was noted to still be lactating, so she did have a recent litter, likely just being weaned from her.

She also had some lumps and masses that we had to remove, and sent out for testing, that came back as benign lumps.

Mea is great with kids and a super kind girl, and is being fostered with dog savvy kids currently.

She isn't great however with other dogs.

When she was surrendered, it was noted she lived with 2 other medium sized dogs.  However, she did have a serious issue, which led to her being surrendered to the shelter and quarantined.

------------------------------------------------------------------
FROM THE SENDING SHELTER:

Mea was brought to us due to a bite quarantine. 

Mea broke out of the front screen door, rushed up to someone walking a Cairn Terrier and shook it in her mouth. 

One person was bit trying to get the dog out of her mouth and another person broke their hand from punching her (she now flinches and kind of melts to the ground when hands are raised over her). 

The victims dog is okay. 

After her quarantine was completed we tested her with cats and dogs – she is quite typical of a boxer when it comes to introductions and playing. She got along okay with a Chihuahua and confident cat, but she does play quite rough and tends to box and stomp so currently I wouldn’t leave her unattended or off-leash with either. 

Medium-large dogs she gets along with great, just very playful and the other dogs need to be tolerant. 

Aside from that her personality is absolutely hysterical. She gets the zoomies quite often and runs around the room with her butt tucked hilariously. 

She POUNCES on squeaky toys, throws treats in the air for herself and LIVES for cuddles. She will climb onto your lap whether you’re on the floor with her or trying to get your work done in an office chair. 

She loves to rest her head on your shoulder and melt into you. 

She has ZERO food/toy/treat aggression and passed her SAFER test with flying colours. 

Mea is an absolute sweetheart and I don’t believe that she deserves to be euthanized over this incident.
------------------------------------------------------------------

However, in foster care, we have seen her reactive with other dogs.  We have not and will not thoroughly test her, for liability purposes and because she's post op from quite a few big surgeries with her mature spay, mass removals and some post op complications, but she gets very excited, wants to lunge, intense vocalization when she sees other dogs.

At this time, we will not place her in a home with other dogs (or cats) and are looking for an adopter that doesn't have a highly populated dog community.  We believe, given her shelter experience, that she can transition in time to get along with other dogs if she's given ongoing training and behaviour modification. 

We will expect adopters to have a training plan in place, to get Mea bettered mannered, so please have that available if you are applying to adopt.

Mea is a very affectionate dog and loves, loves, loves being with her people.  

She has no guarding issues and is a well rounded, kind dog with every human she meets.

FROM HER FOSTER DAD:

She’s cuddly. Playful. 

Very gentle and no guarding of food or toys at all.

I haven’t introduced her to many dogs. Like Tasha she’s excited to go see them but I don’t think she’s had many interactions.  Meeting with my smaller dog did not go well and my dog will stay elsewhere while I'm fostering.

When there’s no other dogs around she walks well but as soon as I see another dog I shorten the leash and have been working on keeping her calm

She’s interacted with my sister‘s dog a few times (medium sized dogs). The first time she growled quite a bit trying to establish dominance etc.

She has been getting better as there’s a lot of dogs in the area as I walk but like I said I’ve been keeping her away from interacting with other dogs for obvious reasons for now

She’s super friendly and gentle with all adults and children

Still has playful puppy tendencies. Obviously does not know her own strength yet.

-----------------------

As of today, though our protocols could change tomorrow, we are still moving forward with adoptions. Our process has changed from some of the previous elements: We are a registered animal welfare organization, so we are deemed an essential service.

All paperwork completed online, video home visits, meet and greets outside respecting social distancing, leashes/collars/supplies wiped down and disinfected (GermiCide 3 wipes), disinfectant on the dog prior to handoff (Aqueos wipes for dogs)

-----------------------

To note: the above description is relevant to this dog in his current setting. Home changes & adopter personalities can bring out different behaviours not previously seen.

We do not specifically kid/cat test our dogs when they arrive at Mattie's Place. That just wouldn't be fair to the dog or child/cat.

We also do not claim, endorse, suggest or hint at, that any of our dogs are hypoallergenic, low shed or no-shed.

Adoption fee includes: spay/neuter, deworming, defleaing, vaccinations, nose to tail health exam, leash|collar, 6 months of preventative based on season/need, DNA test for entertainment purposes, dishes, poop bags, food and any extras she has accumulated in foster care.

animal.description:
MEET PRAX!!

Prax is a strikingly handsome 4 year old male German Shepherd who’s looking for his forever home.

He gets along well with other dogs outside of the home but would really benefit from being the King of his own domain (aka only dog in the home) 

Prax is a very energetic rambunctious boy, he is very eager to please his owners and is VERY loyal. He is alas very protective of his people. He’s not your average house dog...
Prax 100% needs to stay busy and would TRIVE from having a J O B. He will need to be mentally & physically stimulated day in & day out. 

He is presently on a veterinary recommended? Prozac regiment while he’s in foster after previously being surrendered to a shelter where he did not do well. We are getting him re acclimated to life outside of the shelter & life after living with people who had him prior to the shelter. Unfortunately due to improper exercise , lack of mental stimulation, & not proper training practices Prax developed anxiety from not being able to find an “outlet”? that he desperately needed.
?
Prax will need a dedicated owner who is firm & patient who has an active “working” household routine & experienced handing / training dogs of working caliber or mindset. 

We would not recommend homes who have a ton of strangers visit or homes with young children (16yo+only)?

No apartments 
*Rural or more quiet suburban environments? only*

Presently in foster near southern Maryland 

?Interested in adopting??

animal.description:
Need a good laugh? Lenny Bruce is ready to bring all the comedic relief to his forever family!

This little goofball loves people and is very social. His cute antics keep his foster family entertained daily! He is great on a leash, and walks by his person's side. He does well with other dogs too! Lenny is a great mix of active and couch potato. He loves a good game of fetch and enjoys a good snooze on the sofa, too!

Lenny is potty trained and knows lots of tricks like sit, high five, and more! He is learning to love his crate & that counters are not a good place for him to use as a lookout :) He is looking for a home without cats or young children (they just don't understand his humor he says).

Lenny is 2 years old and weighs around 25 pounds. He is vaccinated, microchipped, neutered, heartworm negative, and his adoption fee is $200. To Apply to adopt Lenny, fill out an application on our website! http://mhrindy.org/adoption-inquiry/***Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable so for most of the dogs we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.***

animal.description:
Bizkit has just been welcomed into his Muddy Paws foster family and more information will be available as he settles in over the next couple of weeks. As of now, we think Bizkit may be a bit timid with men, but we know he loves his foster mom! One of his favorite activities is settling in on the couch after a long hard day of supervising her from room to room. Bizkit's also pretty happy to have some kiddos around when it's time to play; however, Bizkit has a lot of energy and is serious about his playtime so he would do best in a home with no children under the age of 10. This little guy is quick on his paws and likes an adventure so he will need a fenced in yard to keep him safe at home! We've discovered that Bizkit gets prettty excited about seeing dogs on television -- his foster mom says he runs up to the tv with his tail wagging, ha! Stay tuned for more updates as we get to know Bizkit.

The suggested adoption donation for Bizkit is $300. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes.

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver.

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months.

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

animal.description:

She was pregnant and gave birth to 13 puppies on Christmas Eve, only days after arriving at a rescue in Grove, OK. Unfortunately 2 of the pups didn't survive, but the other 11 are alive and thriving! Amber and her puppies are now in the very capable hands of a Muddy Paws foster family. Once she is finished caring for her pups, she will be available for a February adoption. We are currently taking applications for pre-approval. She is looking for a furever home where she can be loved unconditionally!

Before applying to adopt Amber, you need to be familiar with your local breed-specific legislation regarding Pit Bulls. Applicants must live within 50 miles of the Omaha/Council Bluffs area.

The suggested adoption donation for Amber is $350. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes.

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver.

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. animal.description: Blueberry is a special little guy. He loves bath mats, cardboard, and soccer balls. He may be a little shy at first but warms up quickly, and LOVES to be around his people. He has some health issues stemming from a neurological disorder that he was born with, including balance and vision, but that doesn't stop him from bouncing around and trying to wrestle with you. Potty training is still in progress, so he would do well in a home with a large yard and some fur siblings to play with. He loves to chew on things and has endless puppy energy, but definitely enjoys hours of just lounging around the house as well. He needs a little extra love and attention so a home where someone is with him most of the time would be ideal. Come meet Blueberry, he would love to be your companion!

animal.description: Hooch would love to be your new best friend! This sweet boy loves to be everywhere you are. He's perfectly happy following you around all day and spending as much time with you as he can! Just give him a bed and a window and he'll be your best co-worker and power napper! His favorite thing to do is to roll around in the grass, sunbathe and 'graze' (he really likes the taste of grass!) He enjoys fetch, tug-of-war, frisbees (really anything he can get his paws on) and has yet to meet a stick he doesn't like. This super smart guy knows a bunch of tricks/commands (sit, shake, down, up, stay, kennel, bed). He is a house-trained boy who is also working on touch and wait commands - who says you can't teach an old dog new tricks! Hooch doesn't socialize well with other dogs, but he loves making new human friends (just take it slow)! As soon as his initial excitement is over, he's all about getting pets and showing off. He loves going on walks. He likes taking it slow in his neighborhood, but is enthusiastic on trails and hikes! And he does really well on a leash as long as you give him enough time to sniff everything. Hooch has some anxiety and takes a little pill for that daily. If you choose to adopt him as your only pup, the APA! Behavior team will be available to help you guide him toward a smooth transition into your home and family life. Come meet this happy boy and see how quickly he'll charm his way into your heart!

animal.description: Daisy is a stocky low rider who is a bit nervous when she first meets new people. She clearly wasn’t treated well early on but she warms up quickly and becomes a goofy, wiggly cuddle bug. This girl loves to cuddle. She’d lie on top of you if you let her. Daisy wants to please and listens well and learns the rules quickly. She is potty trained and mellow in the house and gets along wonderfully with the other female dog and friends dogs that she has been introduced to. She can be aggressive to dogs outside her home or pack so she will need to be on leash or in a yard at all times. She does have some separation anxiety but does well with bones or toys to chew while you are gone. She doesn’t know her own strength and wants to play with excited kids and can knock them down so she will be best in a home with no small kids.

animal.description:
PLEASE READ FIRST: We are located in LOS ANGELES, CA, we DO NOT adopt outside of the Southern California area (as we require physical homechecks), nor will we ship dogs to other parts of the country or out of the country, please do not ask.
 
Hopper and Red are a BONDED PAIR, and need to be adopted together. They lived together outside on a used car since they were puppies. They were recently given up to start a new happier life on this side of the fence. 

They are super sweet, gentle, happy, good looking boys and now are looking for the most amazing forever home to live out their lives. They love long walks and gentle hikes. Red likes to go for little mellow jogs and loves the sunshine while Hopper likes the shade. For two dogs that had never been walked, they are great on leash, no pulling, lunging, barking or whining. They seem to be good with other dogs; they have met several, both small and large and have had no issues, Also no reaction to small children while out on walks. After all the years of living in a crate in a car lot, they love being pet and getting massaged!! They are very bonded and need to stick together.

Both are crate-trained; Red especially loves being in his crate.

If you would like to meet Hopper and Red, please complete our adoption application. Due to Covid-19, our weekly adoption events have been suspended. We do conduct meet-and-greets. All potential adopters must complete our adoption application prior to scheduling a meet-and-greet. You can complete our adoption application online at https://www.tailsofthecityrescue.org/adopt-application

We are located in LOS ANGELES, CA, we DO NOT adopt outside of the Southern California area (as we require physical homechecks), nor will we ship dogs to other parts of the country or out of the country, please do not ask.

animal.description:
Animal Profile: Rusty is estimated to be a 2 year old and a Pit Bull mix who joined us from Texas on 9/26. Rusty was found as a stray in Texas and could have possibly been a backyard dog. He's spent a month with the director of the shelter, coming out of his shell and starting to learn how to trust people. He will need a foster who is patient and can work on his socialization here in the PNW. We will post more info as we get to know him! Rusty is NOT comfortable with children and is looking for a companion that is willing to advocate for him around them.

Seattle Foster Update:
Rusty has been settling in to his foster home really well and would love a home with a playful confident dog to spend his days with but could also make a really good companion as an only dog. Rusty loves the outdoors and would thrive in an active home that enjoys exploring the PNW. Rusty can be a little shy when first approached but with an owner willing to take things slowly and advocate for him in new environments and around new people, he does warm up quickly when approached appropriately.

Here are some of the things Rusty's foster parents have said about him.

He is still very puppy like, so he is a very fun addition to the house.

Car Friendly

Plays well with other dogs

Knows how to sit

comes when he is called

Just wants to please you!

Affection motivated

Goof ball :)

learns quickly

knows how to retrieve his ball/frisbee

house trained

crate trained

Biggest snuggle bug!

loves toys

rides in the car really well

Adoption Info: Adoption fee is $500, which includes spay/neuter, current rabies/DAPPV/bordetella vaccinations, microchip, health certificate, and heartworm test. All adoption fees are donations to a Washington non-profit corporation and all donations go to benefit the animals in our rescue.

Apply online at www.DogGoneSeattle.org

animal.description:
Gunner is about 23 months old (as of 1/11/2021), a Beagle and Wiemaraner Mix from the country of Taiwan.  He weighs 44 pounds and is fully-grown.  Gunner has been living with our foster family in North Wilmington in Delaware since 8/21/2020.   
   
Gunner’s rescued story:

In last October, while a dog rescuer driving on a busy highway in northern Taiwan, she glimpsed a very skinny black dog strayed on the traffic island.  The rescuer pulled over and approached the dog with a can of dog food and some dry food.  Surprisingly, the dog walked toward her soon he saw her; he ate the entire can food quickly and more dry food. 

As the rescuer looked closely, she immediately realized how severely emaciated this black dog was.  He was not only extremely thin, but his body and head covered with many new and old wounds, and some of these wounds were still bleeding.  The dog was very friendly, so she successfully walked him to her car.  We named the dog Gunner as he fights for his life like a brave warrior.

Gunner was brought to the vet hospital for a checkup.  He was about 8-9 months old and only weighed 24 lbs., more than 10 pounds under the ideal weight; he was suffering from severe malnutrition.  Much sadly, the vet confirmed that the wounds on his body were from the knife slash, dog bites and objects cut.

The rescuer concerned if Gunner was a lost dog due to his gentle and mellow disposition; however, she was told about his tragic life by one of her friends living in where Gunner was found.

Gunner originally was one of a litter born by a neglected family mother dog, the owner did not want to spend money spaying the dog and let the dog continue getting pregnant.  None of the mother dog and her puppies were allowed to live inside the house, a cardboard box next to the owner’s house was their shelter. 
 
At the age of 3-4 months old, Gunner already lost all his siblings from being killed by the cars or died from being sickness; he was the only puppy luckily survived.  But, one day Gunner was thrown out into the streets by the owner to let him fend for himself.  Whenever Gunner approached the house, the owner brutely beat him away with a thick stick or a broomstick.  Gunner confused why he was not allowed to go near his mom nor the house.

The neighbors were not nice to Gunner either; they would hit him or scare him away because they think that Gunner would refuse to leave after being fed.  Although Gunner was treated cruelly by his owner and the residents, he never walked far.  He strayed close to his mom, the house, and the owner family because it was the place he grew up and they were the only people he knew.  

Gunner’s completed medical information:

Gunner has received a thorough medical exam; fortunately, he was rescued in time because he was found to have Haemobartonella and Giardia infections.  After three months of treatments, his both infections were cured, and he has been healthy since then.  
Gunner is negative on the following disease and infections: Distemper, SNAP 4Dx (Heartworm, Lyme, Ehrlichia, Anaplasma Phagocytophilum), CBC, Biochemistry blood work, and PCR tests for diseases and infections transmitted by fleas or ticks.  He has also received an x-ray on his hips and joints; he does not have hip dysplasia.  He got his teeth cleaned in August 2020.

Gunner is neutered, de-wormed, up to date on all vaccinations including rabies shot.  He is heartworm negative and on preventative treatment and is micro chipped.  All Gunner's medical documents including his X-ray films on the hips will be given to his adopter when he is adopted.

Gunner’s temperaments and personality:

Although Gunner has a rough start, he never gave up hope and trust on human.  He is one of the most mellow and gentlest dogs we have ever met; he does not have a mean bone in his body.  Gunner has adapted to any new environment very easily, and there is no transition for Gunner.  He is kind and sweet to every creature he met; he just very cherishes any roof provided.

Gunner is a naturally loving and affectionate dog that loves people unconditionally even though he was mistreated by the people whom he loved.  He is super friendly and passionate to strangers and wants to cuddle when he just met the person.  

Although Gunner is almost two years old, sometimes he still acts like a puppy; he loves to communicate or get attention by pawing at people.  Gunner loves to sleep; especially, he loves to snuggle with his foster mom on the bed, but like a little child, Gunner is sleepy in the morning and it is hard to wake him up.  Every morning when the foster mom tries to get Gunner out of bed, he would slip foster mom the paw, “I wanna sleep!”  While the foster mom getting ready in the bathroom, Gunner usually still sleeping.   

Before coming to the USA, Gunner was fostered by a family for nine months, living with two 12 and 13-year-old children, many rescued dogs and three cats; he got along very well with all of them.  Everyone that meets Gunner loves him right away for his well-behavior and easy-going personality.  He is also submissive and listens.  

Gunner loves to play and run with other dogs, and he is often the center of the group while wrestling.  He seems to enjoy such attention from his dog friends, and he has never got upset even though sometimes some of them went too rough.  

Gunner likes to chew dental bones, deer antlers and twigs, but does not seem interested in playing with the ball.  He LOVES food, but he is not food or toy aggressive or possessive toward both people and dogs.  Every time while other dogs are still eating their meals, Gunner already wolfed down his food.  Although he wants other dog’s food, he would politely stand behind the dog and wait patiently to see if he could luckily pick up some kibbles falling from the bowel.  

Gunner does not have separation anxiety; he is fine to stay at home with other dogs.  He is not scared of thunderstorms, fireworks, or other noises, but he is alert; he would bark if there is a dog barking or some noises outside.  He also howls at the answering machine, but he would stop howling when he was called.  

Gunner is very playful but not hyper, he will be a wonderful companion for a moderately-highly active family that likes outdoors activities with children older than 5 years old.  

Gunner needs some outdoors exercise everyday such as long-distance walks, hiking, playing, or running in the yard.  He will not do well in the apartments, condos, or with the retirees’ life paces; he needs a fully enclosed fenced yard, not invisible yard.  People who sharing living space with roommates are not considered by us either. 

Gunner is house broken, walks nicely on leash, and loves car rides; he is calm and well-behaved in the car.

We hope Gunner’s new parents could include him into your outings, short trips, or vacations besides daily walks in the neighborhood, or playing in the back yard.  We wish Gunner could have chance to experience different parts of his life that he had missed before.

How to meet Gunner?

If you are seriously thinking of giving Gunner a loving permanent home, please email us for an application form.  Because all our rescues live with our foster family, we do not accept stop-by visits if you are interested in seeing our dogs.  Before meeting Gunner, the prospective adopter needs to fill out the application and gets approved.

During the state mandated shelter-in-place order BACS has transitioned to virtual, socially-distanced adoptions.
If you have an interest in a particular BACS animal, please email KSwanson@cityofberkeley.info. The first step will be to set up a virtual meeting with their current foster family via phone, zoom, or facetime, to provide you with more detailed information about the animal. Following that, if you feel like it could be a good adoption fit, shelter staff will help coordinate a socially-distanced meeting in person so that you can meet your potential family member up-close and personal. Thank you for your patience during this time. We really appreciate your support!

Torie is a beautiful and active young dog. She gets along great with other dogs, has excellent doggie play skills and may enjoy living in a home with another dog. Torie can be fearful in certain situations and when surprised by unknown people. She needs to live in an adult only home. Torie is smart as a whip and learns quickly so working with a trainer can help her learn to become more comfortable in novel situations and overcome her fears. Torie has so much love to give, with consistency, routine and training she will become a wonderful pet.

animal.description:
Nick came to us after finders neighbors saw him being dumped out of a car in rural MO. He was very shy but found friendships with the fosters family's dogs. He sadly ended up with PARVO and was hospitalized. He is now on the mend and neutered and ready for his forever family. Nick will do best in a home with another dog... he really enjoys having a buddy to play with!! 

ADOPTION INFO
*If you are interested in one of our dogs, please submit an adoption application. 
*If the dog is listed on the pet adoption websites or our website it is available for adoption. 
*Please read the dogs bio to find out details/information on the dog.
*If you meet the requirements for adopting the dog you are interested in we will reach out to you via email/phone. 

Due to the large number of "general inquiries" regarding the adoptable dogs we may not be able to respond, so if you are interested in a particular dog please submit an application for that dog at www.luckyk9.org/adoptable-dogs. 

Our adoption fees vary based on the age of the dog: 
Puppies up to 1yr $350
1 yr to 4 yrs $300
5 to 7 yrs $250
7 yrs and up $200

ALL adoption fees include a clean bill of health from our veterinarian - all pets are current on vaccinations, spayed/neutered, as well as negative for Heartworm (HW) disease and a clear
stool sample. If over 2 mths of age they are on monthly HW & flea/tick prevention. 

ADOPTION REQUIREMENTS: Must own your own home and have a fully fenced back yard - electric or underground fences are not permitted

animal.description:
Please contact JoEllen (sagdinfo@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Chip is a handsome 4-month-old Retriever blend who weighs approximately 20 pounds. He has a sweet temperament and is active and playful. He will make a loyal companion.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for his entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until his puppy cuteness wears off.
You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization. Like most puppies, he may chew on anything within his reach to include but not limited to baseboards, shoes, socks, children's toys, electrical cords, plants, etc.
His adoption fee is $200. This includes his neuter surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccinations, Bravecto, Drontal Plus, Tri-Heart Plus Chewable Tablet, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.
Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.
** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Animal Profile: Hilly is a lab who joined us from Texas on December 30th. She had a rough start in life as she was dumped in the Texas country when she was a young puppy. She was being fed by someone and kept with several other dogs. All the dogs eventually found their way to 4 Legged Friends rescue, and from there she made the trip to Seattle.

When she first arrived Hilly was very afraid, anxious, and confused. She bonds well with other dogs, her companions really help her to come out of her shell. In Texas learned that people are good and they give good attention, but she is still shy when first meeting new people. She will need a home with a confident resident dog to help her feel most comfortable, a securely fenced yard and no young kids.

Seattle Foster Update:
Coming soon!

Adoption Info: Adoption fee is $500, which includes spay/neuter, current rabies/DAPPV/bordetella vaccinations, microchip, health certificate, and heartworm test. All adoption fees are donations to a Washington non-profit corporation and all donations go to benefit the animals in our rescue.

Apply online at www.DogGoneSeattle.org

Animal History: This dog was rescued by 4 Legged Friends Rescue in Texas and transferred via Project Freedom Ride. This dog will be available for adoption in Seattle once evaluated.

animal.description:
Tank was brought into the rescue just before his owners were going to take him to the shelter as they had no time or space for him.  Not sure why the name Tank but perhaps his former family wanted him to have a powerful name to counter his diminutive size.  Tank is two and a half years old and 11 pounds.   He has been vetted, neutered and micro-chipped.   He is a sweet boy who does talk to people using a growling like tone .  He is a Chihuahua/rat terrier mix.
   
He seems to get along fine with other dogs and children, at least teenagers.  He would be fine as an only dog or as part of a pack.   He will bark when playing with other dogs and at times when playing alone with his toys.  We do not think he would be a good fit in an apartment since he does bark at times.

Tank loves to retrieve a tennis ball so needs an adopter who excels at repetitive throwing. On the other hand, he is very much a SNUGGLER, a true lap dog and likes to sleep in his foster mother’s bed.  She is trying to teach him boundaries as he prefers to be as close as possible.

If you think you can provide a good home to this little guy, please go to www.freedomstreetrescue.org to complete an application. or email rhondabarron@earthlink.net for an app.   He is located in Houston, Texas and will come to his new home by professional transport.

animal.description:
If you don’t want to start from scratch with a puppy and you want a stalwart friend by your side at all times, then an adult dog may be the best choice you ever make. We’ve all heard the phrase, “You can’t teach an old dog new tricks,” but that couldn’t be further from the truth. Adult dogs have a great attention span and eagerness to please, allowing them to learn faster than more youthful members of their species. If you’re looking for a steadfast companion who will be truly grateful for a second chance at a happy life, consider adopting a dog. 

Fauna is a strong, German Shepherd who needs an adopter familiar with the breed. She has resource guarding issues over her food bowl and potentially other resources she finds to have high value .Fauna would do best in a household with older teens able to take direction. Young children may be in jeopardy around food items or food dropped on the floor. Fauna can be introduced to other dogs but does not solicit play.(selective). No cats.

animal.description:
Roxie
3 Years Old
Natural Tail
Crate trained
Basic obedience in progress
Walks well on leash
Mellow male dog friendly
Cats unknown
Kid friendly
Fostered in Camas, WA

Hi! I'm Roxie! I am a sweet, loving young girl. I like being outside and I walk well on a leash but I also learn my surroundings and love roaming free in the yard, checking everything out. I can find out a lot of things by using my nose and ears. I recall when you say my name, and since I don't like to be too far from you, I'm easy to keep track of! I don't really play with toys outside, but I do like to have stuffed animals and chews when I'm inside. And I like going on car rides!

My best talent is being a companion and sharing all my love with whomever is around. I am very gentle and love being touched. I will curl up by your feet and snooze happily while you're reading or watching TV. You don't have to worry about me getting on the furniture all the time because I need help, so unless you want to invite me, I will stay on my bed or on the carpet. I'm currently on thyroid medication and can be a little anxious just because everything is so new. However, I'm learning that people can be so nice and that I can trust them! If you would like a very sweet companion to just go on strolls and become your best friend, I'm volunteering!

From foster Mom - Roxie is really coming out of her shell and is a wonderful girl. She is a little shy at first and still unsure of her surroundings but is generally quite calm and loving and just wants to be wherever you are. She needs to have her family around to help her figure her surroundings out and help her feel secure for a while. Her vision is currently impaired, but will hopefully be improving soon. Roxie is scheduled for cataract surgery in Vancouver, WA so she is looking for a foster to adopt home near there! If she sounds like your girl - please fill out an application today. You won't be disappointed!

Bit.ly/WHBRadopt

www.Wigglinhomeboxerrescue.org
Email: wigglinhomeboxerrescue@gmail.com
Phone (360) 723-0219

animal.description: Meet affectionate, upbeat, friendly and playful Nala!  This 65lb beauty is just 2 years old and was rescued from South Korea by Greyhound Pets in Woodinville.  She is a darling “fuzzy” not your typical greyhound, maybe mix of retriever or pointer?!  Nala is an amazing love bug who needs a very active home with a securely fenced yard.  Her previous adopter ran and biked with her, both of which she loved. Unfortunately, his circumstances changed and he can no longer keep Nala- therefore she is looking for her truly forever home now.  Loyal and social Nala is curious, fearless, fast and agile.  Smart and young Nala is eager to learn and a real pleaser.  She is affectionate and outgoing and enjoys anything outdoors! She loves car rides!  Nala does ok with other dogs, but she plays fast and furious and does best with sturdier, larger, non-greyhound breeds. Nala is perfectly happy to be the only dog as well as she digs your companionship and your one-on-one activities.  As a greyhound mix, Nala has some prey drive and therefore needs a home without cats.  Nala has been friendly to children she has met when out and about, but she may be too active for toddlers who she could knock over.  Nala’s adoption fee is $500 and she is available to meet at Greyhound Pets in Woodinville. Nala is spayed, vaccinated and micro-chipped. For questions or to set up a meet and greet, contact Kathy at kkreyling11@yahoo.com and please use the link for our adoption application: https://www.greyhoundpetsinc.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/02/Adoption_Application_2020-Revised-Website.pdf.  Loving and lovable Nala is the most deserving and fun adventure girl who deserves you and your active northwest family!

animal.description: Meet medium size and medium energy Brock who would love a serene and calm place to retire.  Brock was adopted over 6 years ago after he was rescued by RCR and transported from a high kill shelter in Georgia to Washington state.  Sadly, now 8-year-old Brock is again looking for his forever home as his owner of 6 years has a new girlfriend who doesn’t like Brock.  Jack Russell mix Brock is back with his former foster in Moses Lake while he awaits a patient and loving adopter who has no other pets or children. Brock weighs just 28lbs and is still as active and playful as he was years ago. He’s had a lot of changes lately, so Brock needs an adopter who is knowledgeable about fearful dogs and who is willing to give him time to adjust. Brock is skittish and reactive to loud noises and sudden moves. He likes daily walks and needs an enclosed, fenced in yard. Brock is a pretty calm boy once he feels comfortable with you and will gladly be a couch potato with you or more likely your lap warmer. If you give him the ability and space to choose the amount and type of interaction he wants, he thrives!  Brock craves attention and loves to snuggle. He would love to be with a single person who is without kids and is not away from home for too many hours a day.  Brock is totally house trained and crate-trained. He gets along well with other dogs after proper intros, but really just prefers being with you, his people! Brock happily sleeps and hangs out in his crate.  Brock is very food motivated and is very smart.  He knows his basic commands and sits before going in a door and on command. He is also quite good with “stay” and will give you his “paw”. Brock LOVES squeaker toys! Loud and sudden noises seem to remind him of his past and startle him which makes us assume it wasn't a very happy past. This is Brock’s last chance at finding an experienced and caring adopter who can make Brock the center of their world. We are hoping that we can find Brock a home that will guarantee him a happy future. Brock's adoption fee is $150 and he is neutered, micro-chipped and fully-vaccinated.  For questions and a conversation with his foster mom Lindsey, please email rcrlindsey@gmail.com. Brock is currently being fostered in Moses Lake, WA. To complete an application, go to www.raincityrescue.com/adopt.  Best boy Brock might be a bit complicated, but if you need a project and to help save a life- Brock will be totally worth your time to check out.  He will repay you with kisses and loves and gratitude forever!

animal.description:
Sweet Abbey is ready to find her furever home. She has been with us for about three weeks now and has adapted so well to being in a new home and out of the shelter. She has proven herself to be a loyal and loving girl with a hint of rambunctious. She loves her humans and we are anxious to find her a home where she can build bonds that will last forever. 

Unfortunately, Abbey was surrendered to a SC shelter by her owner due to medical challenges, but she wasted no time befriending her new foster family and instantly became attached. Although she struggled with anxiety for a little while, we have since seen her amazing spunky personality emerge. Abbey loves going on walks, taking car rides, and snuggling up with her stuffed animals at the end of the day. She recently mastered the art of fetch and needs a big yard to run around in, especially when her “zoomies” come on. Abbey craves attention and we would love for her to find a family who can shower her with pets and belly rubs throughout the day. Although Abbey does great on a leash, she is fairly strong and should be placed with someone who is prepared for occasional pulling when she gets excited. Abbey is an absolute sweetheart and is bound to melt your heart. 


PLEASE NOTE:  While this Lab may not be available for adoption by the time you complete the adoption process, other great Labs are always finding their way into our Rescue. 

For more information on this Lab, please contact INFO@BROOKLINELABRESCUE.ORG.  

If you are interested in adopting this Lab or any other Lab from our Rescue, please visit our Web site, www.brooklinelabrescue.org, for more information on our adoption process. If you need additional information about the adoption process or whether you are in our coverage area, please send an e-mail to our Rescue at info@brooklinelabrescue.org

Even if you are not ready to adopt, you can still help us help our Labs!

Brookline Labrador Retriever Rescue is a 501(c)3 non-profit volunteer organization funded entirely by donations. Donations are always needed to help with veterinary costs, transportation, and supplies for our dogs. For information on donating to BLRR please click here. Donations are accepted via PayPal or you can mail a check to: Brookline Labrador Retriever Rescue, P.O. Box 638, Warrington, PA 18976-0638

animal.description:
OUR ADOPTION PROCESS AND APPLICATION ARE AVAILABLE AT WWW.SOHODOGRESCUE.ORG AND OUR ADOPTION FEE IS $275

Pippa is a sweet, happy Cattle Dog girl who is full of "go"!  She is 5 years young, weighs about (40) lbs, and she is crate-trained and house-broken.  Pippa walks nicely on leash and she is great in the car.  Pippa is a wonderful girl at home with her people.  This little athlete is super smart and loves to learn all kinds of new tricks.  She has so much personality, and she will make you laugh with her antics as much as she will charm you with her sweetness. Pippa is also a medium-to-high energy girl who would be a great companion for hikers, bikers, and runners - here's your chance for a top-notch companion!  She LOVES to go for a run with her human.
Cattle Dog enthusiasts know how strongly they will bond with one person. Pippa has that quality with just a slight twist.  She will gladly share her human with other humans, but she is selective when it comes to sharing her human with other dogs.  We are therefore looking for a home for Pippa where she can be the only dog, at least to start.  Also, because she can be a bit nippy (like most ACDs), any children in her new family should be over the age of 12.  For those who love Australian Cattle Dogs, this little girl is a classic example of the breed. 
Now the caveat: Pippa most likely has glaucoma. Glaucoma is a treatable condition that causes pressure on the eye, and it makes dogs feel like they have a constant migraine headache. She needs daily eye drops which are not very expensive, but will be needed for the rest of her life.  She will also require yearly visits to an eye specialist.  We are working with eye specialists now so that we can get a treatment plan set up for her, which is not easy in this COVID world where all the vets seem to have incredibly busy schedules!  
This is where a very rare foster-to-adopt opportunity comes in! We don't feel that there is any advantage to Pippa to hold her in a foster home when she could be bonding with a new family.   However, we need to continue to be responsible for her eye care until she is stable on a long-term treatment plan.  Our solution is to find a forever home for Pippa, with the understanding that the adoption won't be "official" until we have a complete diagnosis and treatment plan. We are looking for an energetic new family for Pippa near a major metropolitan area where we can find an eye specialist to continue this work.  You, as a foster-to-adopt family, will benefit from our knowledge base, have expert guidance with our trainers, and we will foot the vet care bills for her specialized care until we get a final maintenance plan from the eye specialist.
Pippa has really lit up the lives of her foster family, and she will do the same for her new family. She is a keenly intelligent, sassy little girl and we want her to stay that way for years to come! If you are interested in Pippa, please apply today!  Pippa is in Chesapeake, VA

animal.description:
Hi there!  My name is MILO.  What’s yours?  Nice to meet ya!  

WATCH MY VIDEO:  https://youtu.be/C6OmmW1qWzY

https://youtu.be/7j6NvJyryLo

A nice person came along and took me in and, now, I am ready to hit the road to your house!  Uh, make that “our” house, OK?  I definitely need a house with a fenced-in yard cuz I need room to run and romp and be safe!  The rescue requires (1) a fenced-in yard and (2) a vet reference from a vet that you have used for a current or previous dog to be sure that all vetting was done and (3) a comparable-sized doggie sibling)  

I am a Retriever/Staffy mix.  I am 10 MONTHS old and I weigh 55-60 pounds. I have been neutered and am up to date on vaccines so I'm ready to go to my new home with YOU!!  Those funny-looking 2-legged creatures said I’m also microchipped – whatever THAT is.  At any rate, I am fully vetted.  Is that anything close to petted?  I love to be petted!  They say I'm precious.  Hmmm, Is my name Milo or Precious?

Wanna hear some more good stuff about me?  OK, here goes.  I like ALL people and ALL dogs.  I need to have a DOGGIE SIBLING about my size so we can run and romp together and burn up LOTS and LOTS of energy!   I know basic commands.  I respond very well to consistent, positive reinforcement training and I'm a good learner!  Smart, huh?

I am attentive, affectionate, silly, playful and loyal.  I LOVE cuddles, car rides, holding hands and tummy rubs.  I am a beta doggie.  I back down when prompted by aggressive dogs. I'm an amazing companion!

I have lots to learn.  Will you teach me all the things a pup needs to know to be safe and happy? I LOVE to give kisses so get ready!  

If you have children, then need to be older children - 12 and up because I like to play hard and run fast!  It's fun!

I like to take naps when I'm tired from playing.  I need  love, exercise and couch-sitting when we get tired!  Let's be a team, OK?

If you would like to take me home (and you know you do), please email rescuedogsgalore@gmail.com  and they can get me on my way to a new and loving home!  My adoption fee is $150 and includes my vetting, neutering, and a microchip.

animal.description:
Hi, I'm Bobo! I'm a happy-go-lucky boy looking for my forever home! 

I am a medium to high energy dog that loves walks and am leash and crate trained. I am house trained, have basic obedience skills, and would love to learn more because I am eager to please and I love treats! I'm gentle taking food from your hand. I like to swim and go for car rides - I'm always up for an adventure! I love my squeaky toy, but sometimes I need a reminder not to get TOO excited. 

I'm happy to lay around and cuddle with you, I'm very affectionate. I love having my ears massaged and my belly rubbed. I really like meeting new people, but sometimes I get just a little too excited and need to be reminded not to jump. I'm good with people, but not sure about other dogs, my foster parents haven't seen me with other dogs yet. They do know I'm not a fan of felines, and this one time an opossum was in the backyard, and I didn't really like him. Speaking of yards, I would love a big yard with a six foot fence. Sometimes loud noises scare me - darn fireworks! 

I am looking for a loving and affectionate forever home that is patient and willing to work with me on my few little quirks. I'm want to be your fur-ever boy!

BoBo is 3 years old, 83 lbs, and ready for his forever home! Please visit www.liveloveanimalrescue.org to fill out an adoption application.

Heather is a beautiful 2 year old Mountain Cur & Terrier mix in need of a new home! Heather was brought to the shelter extremely emaciated and in need of some TLC. She is very kind and sweet and seems to do well with her kennel mates. Heather enjoys going for walks and playing with her shelter family.

To view the adoptable dogs at our shelter, you must fill out an adoption application found on our website. Due to the COVID-19 pandemic, we are showing dogs on an appointment only basis. Please understand that we are receiving a high volume of applications at this time and are doing our best to address as many as we can. Please be patient. Thank you.

The adoption fee for adult dogs is $250. Aside from the shelter, food and water, exercise and compassion they receive while in our care, this also includes veterinary services such as Rabies, Distemper+Lepto, Bordetella, H3N2/H3N8 Influenza, heartworm testing, fecal exams, preventions and deworming medications. Spays/Neuters are also included as part of the adoption fee as is microchipping. 
Puppies under the age of 6 months have an adoption fee of $350. The veterinary services rendered include puppies first round of vaccines, fecal exams, deworming medications, preventions, and microchipping. Our facility spays and neuters dogs at 6 months of age. If the puppy is adopted prior to his, or her prescheduled surgery date, a $200 spay/neuter deposit will be taken on the day of adoption. This deposit it refundable and will be returned to the adopter once proof of the procedure is returned to the shelter. 
COVID-19 NOTE: Please understand that we are looking for forever home for our pets. We understand that many people have a lot of time on their hands during the COVID-19 pandemic, so this may seem like an ideal time to bring home a new pet. Please be sure you are prepared to give your new pet his, or her forever home once our lives go back to normal. They deserve it. Thank you and stay safe.

animal.description:
Nia. 

Where do we even begin? We got a call from a community member that there had been a dog living on a hill along a rail line. The dog was fearful so would run away when the Good Samaritan would try to get her. We ended up going out to the rail line..... the situation was near impossible but after a 3/4 mile walk down the active tracks, we reached her. It took some coaxing and patience, but we were able to get a slip lead around her neck; we called her to come the rest of the way down the hill, snd she melted into a loving dog, that was relieved to be out of the elements. Before we scanned for a chip, we took the horrible, heavy pinch collar off of her. 

No tags, no chip and no owner came forward so........ she gets a new great home!!!!! 
 
This girl is truly special. Nia is about 5 years old and approx 40#. She has been with her foster family several weeks now and she’s ready for her fresh start. Nia is great with dogs of all sizes as well as cats. She’s extremely loyal to her people, is smart, knows basic manners but can pull a tad on lead. She can be active and playful but also enjoys a snooze. Nia enjoys natural bones, Nyla bones, balls and squeak toys. She loves all people and is truly a deserving girl that will be a fantastic family member to a family. 

Nia is vaccinated, spayed, chipped and ready for the right home. If you’re interested in adoption, please complete the following link. Her adoption fee is $225. Adoption application.  https://form.jotform.com/careforpets/cfp-adoption-application

animal.description:
Red is a 7 year old spayed female chihuahua/feist mix who weighs about 25 lbs. Red was rescued from a hoarding situation along with 27 other dogs. After enduring so much neglect in her life, she can be very shy at first and is looking for an experienced, quiet, patient family that will take things slowly with her as she settles in. Once she settles in, Red is an easy-going, well-mannered girl. We have loved watching her blossom in her foster home with the love and care she was deprived of for so long. Red is crate-trained, housebroken, and walks well on a leash. She does well with other dogs after a slow, proper introduction but wouldn't mind being the center of her family's attention. She isn't interested in playing with other dogs at all, just exists with them. In her foster home, she has learned how fun it is to play with soft squeaky toys with her people. Once she feels safe, Red enjoys getting pets and scratches from her people and will curl up next to her foster family for more attention. She's almost bossy with her requests for attention and snuggles. We have no doubt that Red will make a wonderful companion - all she needs is a chance! Please help us find Red the amazing forever family she's waited her whole life for!

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/
We are a foster based organization, so we do not have a facility to visit. Please read our FAQs to learn more: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/faq
Follow us on Facebook for foster updates and a full list of our adoptable pets: https://www.facebook.com/all4pawsrescue/

animal.description:
JoJo is a beautiful mixed breed pup, who likely has some mastiff in her. She weighs about 60 lbs and is likely 2-3 years old.

JoJo loves her foster dads and they have thoroughly enjoyed having her, but their landlord has breed restrictions and won't let them adopt her. So she's on the market and hoping to find her forever home soon before the landlord kicks her out!

She LOVES playing ball and loves car rides. She is very affectionate with her humans, but not quite comfortable with other dogs yet. With time, proper introductions, and professional training, she likely would overcome her fear of other dogs and live with another one... however, in the meantime, we prefer she be adopted as an only dog. She has not been cat tested or kid tested, but we will not adopt her to a home with young children.

JoJo has been spayed, vaccinated, microchipped, and is heartworm negative. Her adoption fee is $300. If you are interested in adopting JoJo, please submit an application on our website, www.prodogsohio.org/adoptables.

She's being fostered in the Dayton area. Please note, we only schedule meet and greets with approved applicants. We are not currently hosting adoption events due to Covid.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
We appreciate your support, in order to help us continue to rescue dogs! Donations can be made via our PayPal account - info@prodogsohio.org.
You must be willing to commute to the location that the pet is being fostered in order to be eligible to adopt. We do not ship our pets. We also require that you personally bring the pet back to us should the adoption not work out.
We do NOT negotiate adoption fees. All money goes to support our rescue operation. We are 100% volunteered based.
We require your current dog(s) to be current on vaccines and heartworm prevention.
Apply online at www.prodogsohio.org, under the Adoptables tab.
Due to the volume of apps and inquiries, we may not be able to respond to everyone.

animal.description:
Hi Everyone WAFFLES here are you looking for a side of breakfast to go with your life cause I may be the one for you!

My life had been not so good before this rescue came to save me from that awful dog jail place.

I belonged to a family who made me live outside and didn't treat me to good.

They also didn't care to keep me safely secured so I ended up at the pound and they were notified but let me sit there in that place for 8 MONTHS and it was scary!

They finally came yay.....but..... they acted all annoyed and a bit angry and it was real obvious to the people there that they really didn't want to be bothered with me anymore but they took me home anyway.
No one knows if they just put me on the streets or what because a few months later I was on the streets and turned into to dog jail AGAIN. ARGH!

And I sat and waited, and waited. AND WAITED. They never came to get me and my time there was pretty much up!

Thankfully the pound and volunteers all called this rescue cause I'm such a good boy they wanted me to go to a RESCUE so I'd go to a GOOD HOME.

So here I am, I'm READY to be the WAFFLES to your BREAKFAST dish!

I'm a 3 year old 70 pound beautiful and sweet bully boy who is house and crate trained and good on a leash but I need a strong leader to continue to teach me what I need to know since my first owners used me as a backyard lawn ornament.

I'm good with other dogs my size but should be in a home with no kids or small dogs or cats.

My most favorite thing to do is to snuggle, get petted and give kisses!

I do need someone with experience with my breed and to go slow and give me a little time but once I know you are not gonna hurt me I will be your bestest friend and always want to be at your side!

If you think we might be a good match please go to www.bulliesandbuddies.com and fill out an application to ADOPT me ok?
Hope to meet ya soon!
Love,
WAFFLES 

I am in the Southern CA area-sorry but my rescue does NOT adopt out of state
